"title": "1351: covenant, God's with David",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1351",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God's promise to establish David and his descendants on Israel's throne for ever. It provided Israel with a basis for the hope of deliverance and restoration, and became a focus for the Messianic expectation which was fulfilled, ultimately, in Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>God's promise to establish David's line</h2>\n<h3>God's election of David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:70\">PSA 78:70</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:21\">2SA 6:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:16\">1KI 8:16</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:6\">2CH 6:6</a></p>\n<h3>God's covenant is everlasting</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:3-Ps89:4\">PSA 89:3–89:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:11-2Sam7:16\">2SA 7:11–7:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:5\">2SA 23:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:45\">1KI 2:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:5\">2CH 13:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:50\">PSA 18:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:28-Ps89:29\">PSA 89:28–89:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:35-Ps89:37\">PSA 89:35–89:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:17\">JER 33:17</a></p>\n<h3>God's covenant is inherited through obedience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:11-Ps132:12\">PSA 132:11–132:12</a></strong> <em>Though God's promise to maintain David's throne is unbreakable, individual descendants must continue to be faithful if they are to inherit the blessings promised to David.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:25-1Kgs8:26\">1KI 8:25–8:26</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:16-2Chr6:17\">2CH 6:16–6:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:4-1Kgs9:5\">1KI 9:4–9:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:17-2Chr7:18\">2CH 7:17–7:18</a></p>\n<h3>God's covenant blessings are forfeited through disobedience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:4-Jer22:5\">JER 22:4–22:5</a></strong> <em>Failure to remain faithful to God brings judgment on the royal house and the people.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:6-1Kgs9:9\">1KI 9:6–9:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:19-2Chr7:22\">2CH 7:19–7:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:11-1Kgs11:13\">1KI 11:11–11:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:31-1Kgs11:33\">1KI 11:31–11:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:24-Jer7:26\">JER 7:24–7:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:6-Jer22:9\">JER 22:6–22:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer36:30-Jer36:31\">JER 36:30–36:31</a></p>\n<h3>God's promise is fulfilled by grace</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr21:7\">2CH 21:7</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs8:19\">2KI 8:19</a> <em>Though particular kings may suffer God's anger because of their sin, God's faithfulness to the house of David as a whole, and thus to the nation of Israel, will continue.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:34-1Kgs11:36\">1KI 11:34–11:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:39\">1KI 11:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:4\">1KI 15:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:30-Ps89:34\">PSA 89:30–89:34</a></p>\n<h2>The Davidic covenant as a basis for hope</h2>\n<h3>God's election of Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:7\">2KI 21:7</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:7\">2CH 33:7</a> <em>God's Name signifies his presence. God's choice of David was closely related to his choice of Jerusalem, the city established by David, as the place where the divine presence symbolised in the temple and the ark of the covenant was to be found.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:20-1Kgs8:21\">1KI 8:20–8:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:10-2Chr6:11\">2CH 6:10–6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:32\">1KI 11:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:36\">1KI 11:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:25\">1CH 23:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:41-2Chr6:42\">2CH 6:41–6:42</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:8-Ps132:10\">PSA 132:8–132:10</a></p>\n<h3>God's promise to defend Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:35\">ISA 37:35</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:34\">2KI 19:34</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:20\">2KI 19:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech12:7-Zech12:9\">ZEC 12:7–12:9</a></p>\n<h3>God's promise to restore David's house</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:11\">AMO 9:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:16\">ACT 15:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:25-Jer33:26\">JER 33:25–33:26</a></p>\n<h2>Hopes expressed in the Davidic covenant are focused in the Messiah</h2>\n<h3>The Messiah fulfils the Davidic hope</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:5-Jer23:6\">JER 23:5–23:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1-Ps110:2\">PSA 110:1–110:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:7\">ISA 9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:1-Isa11:2\">ISA 11:1–11:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:5\">ISA 16:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:3\">ISA 55:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:23-Ezek34:25\">EZK 34:23–34:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:8\">ZEC 3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:42\">JHN 7:42</a></p>\n<h3>God's promise to David fulfilled in Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:32-Luke1:33\">LUK 1:32–1:33</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:16\">REV 22:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:1\">MAT 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:41-Matt22:46\">MAT 22:41–22:46</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:35-Mark12:37\">MRK 12:35–12:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:41-Luke20:44\">LUK 20:41–20:44</a>MRK <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:10\">11:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:9\">MAT 21:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:21\">LUK 24:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:6\">ACT 1:6</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:29-Acts2:31\">ACT 2:29–2:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:34\">ACT 13:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:3\">ROM 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:8\">2TI 2:8</a></p>",
